00:41:17.311 --> 00:41:18.830
that doesn't make sense.

00:41:18.830 --> 00:41:23.466
So if we are talking about
raising a happy person,

00:41:23.466 --> 00:41:26.664
how do you raise a person
who is a critical thinker

00:41:26.664 --> 00:41:30.280
and is not getting happy because
of the state of the world?

00:41:30.280 --> 00:41:32.280
TREMAINE DU PREEZ: That
is a brilliant question.

00:41:32.280 --> 00:41:34.560
And my son has already
hit up against this.

00:41:34.560 --> 00:41:37.890
Brexit-- he is so
unhappy about Brexit.

00:41:37.890 --> 00:41:40.590
And he can't understand Brexit.

00:41:40.590 --> 00:41:42.240
And he's in an
international school.

00:41:42.240 --> 00:41:43.270
He grew up in Asia.

00:41:43.270 --> 00:41:44.220
He loves England.

00:41:44.220 --> 00:41:45.690
And then Brexit happens.

00:41:45.690 --> 00:41:47.430
And he's trying
to understand it.

00:41:47.430 --> 00:41:49.320
Now, this is theory of mind.

00:41:49.320 --> 00:41:51.450
This is the ability
to say that I

00:41:51.450 --> 00:41:53.160
have a certain way of thinking.

00:41:53.160 --> 00:41:55.290
And for me, that is
logical and correct.

00:41:55.290 --> 00:41:57.630
And there's a big question
about what is logical

00:41:57.630 --> 00:41:59.967
and what is rationality.

00:41:59.967 --> 00:42:01.800
But I have to respect
that other people have

00:42:01.800 --> 00:42:03.660
a different way of
thinking because

00:42:03.660 --> 00:42:05.400
of their different
frames and filters

00:42:05.400 --> 00:42:08.040
and where they were raised
and how they were brought up.

00:42:08.040 --> 00:42:11.070
So part of that maturity
and that ability

00:42:11.070 --> 00:42:13.380
to be happy with my life
is to know that this

00:42:13.380 --> 00:42:15.150
is my decision making.

00:42:15.150 --> 00:42:17.940
And these are the boundaries
within which I work.

00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:21.060
I cannot affect everybody
else's thinking.

00:42:21.060 --> 00:42:22.050
So you know--

00:42:22.050 --> 00:42:23.550
AUDIENCE: But they
can affect yours.

00:42:23.550 --> 00:42:24.220
TREMAINE DU PREEZ: Absolutely.

00:42:24.220 --> 00:42:24.505
Absolutely.

00:42:24.505 --> 00:42:25.662
AUDIENCE: That's the
problem I'm talking about.

00:42:25.662 --> 00:42:26.490
TREMAINE DU PREEZ: Yeah, Yes.

00:42:26.490 --> 00:42:28.680
But if you know that you're
making the right decisions--

00:42:28.680 --> 00:42:29.280
you see--

00:42:29.280 --> 00:42:31.350
and this is the coach in me--

00:42:31.350 --> 00:42:33.870
nobody can make you unhappy.

00:42:33.870 --> 00:42:35.900
You choose to be unhappy.

00:42:35.900 --> 00:42:38.210
And it's easy for me to
say that, sitting up there.

00:42:38.210 --> 00:42:39.850
I know that.

00:42:39.850 --> 00:42:42.772
But again, it is that choice.

00:42:42.772 --> 00:42:44.730
And the minute somebody
else makes you unhappy,

00:42:44.730 --> 00:42:49.200
it's a powerlessness
that you're accepting.

00:42:49.200 --> 00:42:52.590
So again, that critical thinker
in you-- because emotions

00:42:52.590 --> 00:42:56.700
are about 60% of our
thinking, of our decisions.

00:42:56.700 --> 00:42:58.920
And that emotional
content that is coming in

00:42:58.920 --> 00:43:01.290
is not making you happy.

00:43:01.290 --> 00:43:02.540
And you're giving power to it.

00:43:02.540 --> 00:43:04.260
So the idea is to
understand, well,

00:43:04.260 --> 00:43:06.780
what power do I have
over other people,

00:43:06.780 --> 00:43:08.590
and then being able
to step away and say,

00:43:08.590 --> 00:43:09.760
this is my decision making.

00:43:09.760 --> 00:43:10.570
And it's good.

00:43:10.570 --> 00:43:12.600
You cannot change other
people's thinking,

00:43:12.600 --> 00:43:14.760
as much as we cannot
change Brexit.

00:43:14.760 --> 00:43:16.350
But it's what we do with that.

00:43:16.350 --> 00:43:18.840
I got so unhappy with
Singapore and Hong

00:43:18.840 --> 00:43:21.810
Kong having the top two
education systems in the world

00:43:21.810 --> 00:43:22.920
that I wrote a book.

00:43:22.920 --> 00:43:24.540
And I feel better about it.

00:43:24.540 --> 00:43:26.100
Because I'm doing
something about it.

00:43:26.100 --> 00:43:28.140
Because it used to
drive me insane that--

00:43:28.140 --> 00:43:29.100
I went looking.

00:43:29.100 --> 00:43:31.650
Because schools keep saying
they teach critical thinking.

00:43:31.650 --> 00:43:32.760
I was going, really?

00:43:32.760 --> 00:43:34.882
Let me see what
they're teaching.

00:43:34.882 --> 00:43:36.840
And it turns out that
what schools are teaching

00:43:36.840 --> 00:43:39.840
is a critical application
or a real world application

